Sentencas: Perovskite La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3+delta(LSCF) as a promising cathode material possessed overwhelming electronic conduction along with certain ionic conductivity.
Titulo: Validating the efficiency of γ-Al2O3/La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ double-layer electrolyte for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Its strong electron conduction capability hinder the application of pure-phase LSCF as electrolyte in semiconductor membrane fuel cell (SMFC).
Titulo: Validating the efficiency of γ-Al2O3/La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ double-layer electrolyte for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In order to constrain the electron transport and take advantage of the decent ion conduction of LSCF, a thin layer of gamma-Al2O3 with insulating property was added as an electron barrier layer and combine with LSCF to forma two-layer structure electrolyte.
Titulo: Validating the efficiency of γ-Al2O3/La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ double-layer electrolyte for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Through adjusting the weight ratio of LSCF/gamma-Al2O3 to optimize the thickness of double layers, an open circuit voltage of 0.98 V and a maximum power density of 690 mW/cm(2) was received at 550 degrees C. At the same time, SEM, EIS and other characterization technology had proven that the LSCF/gamma-Al2O3 bi-layer electrolyte can work efficiently at low temperature.
Titulo: Validating the efficiency of γ-Al2O3/La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ double-layer electrolyte for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The advantage of this work is the application of double-layer (gamma-Al2O3/LSCF) structure electrolyte to instead of mixed material electrolyte in lowtemperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Validating the efficiency of γ-Al2O3/La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ double-layer electrolyte for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Structural innovation and the using of insulating materials provided clues for the further development of SMFC.
Titulo: Validating the efficiency of γ-Al2O3/La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ double-layer electrolyte for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell
